ol\"|Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadianhot100|4|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=2010-08-27|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadaac|8|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=December 5, 2017|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadachrtop40|8|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=December 5, 2017|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadacountry|1|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=December 5, 2017|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcanadahotac|2|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=December 5, 2017|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland3|98|artist=Carrie Underwood|rowheader=true|accessdate=January 30, 2020}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|8|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=2010-08-27|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardadultcontemporary|6|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=2010-08-27|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardadultpopsongs|5|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=2010-08-27|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardcountrysongs|1|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=2010-08-27|rowheader=true}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardpopsongs|9|artist=Carrie Underwood|accessdate=2010-08-27|rowheader=true}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2006)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US Country Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2006/hot-country-songs| title=Best of 2006: Country Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] | year=2006| accessdate=July 10, 2012}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 37\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n!Chart (2007)\n!Position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2007/hot-100-songs?begin=1&order=position|title=Billboard Hot 100 Year-End 2007|accessdate=2012-04-15}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|6\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US Adult Contemporary (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2007/adult-contemporary-songs|title=Adult Contemporary Songs \u2013 Year-End 2007|work=Billboard|accessdate=September 21, 2019}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US Adult Top 40 (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2007/adult-pop-songs|title=Adult Pop Songs \u2013 Year-End 2007|work=Billboard|accessdate=September 21, 2019}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|16\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|US Country Songs (''Billboard'')<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2007/hot-country-songs| title=Best of 2007: Country Songs | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] | year=2007| accessdate=July 11, 2012}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 51\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Certifications==\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=single|region=Canada|artist=Carrie Underwood |title=Before He Cheats|award=Platinum|certyear=2007|relyear=2006|accessdate=August 23, 2013|digital=true}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=single|region=United Kingdom|artist=Carrie Underwood |title=Before He Cheats|award=Silver|relyear=2006|certyear=2018|refname=\"ukcert\"}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=single|region=United States|artist=Carrie Underwood |title=Before He Cheats|award=Platinum|number=6|relyear=2006|certyear=2015|salesamount=4,483,000 |salesref=<ref name=\"us sales\"/>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|nosales=true|streaming=true}}\n\n== In pop culture ==\n\n* 2010 the song is played in the [[CBS]] police procedural series ''[[Cold Case]]'', season 7 episode \"[[List of Cold Case episodes|Two Weddings]]\"<ref>{{Citation|title=\"Cold Case\" Two Weddings (TV Episode 2010)|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1580053/soundtrack|access-date=2018-06-26}}</ref>\n\n*In the ''[[Family Guy]]'' episode \"[[Stewie Goes for a Drive]]\", Brian and Stewie listen to the song whilst in a car near the start of the episode. Stewie confesses to being a fan. He eventually sings along to the song after Brian leaves him in the car, and shortly afterwards, says he should be on ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''.{{Citation needed|date=August 2019}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MetroLyrics song|carrie-underwood|before-he-cheats}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Carrie Underwood singles}}\n\n[[Category:2006 singles]]\n[[Category:2005 songs]]\n[[Category:Arista Nashville singles]]\n[[Category:Billboard Hot Country Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Carrie Underwood songs]]\n[[Category:Country ballads]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Roman White]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Mark Bright (record producer)]]\n[[Category:Songs about infidelity]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Chris Tompkins]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Josh Kear]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2006 single by Carrie Underwood}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Before He Cheats\n| cover      = Carrie Underwood - Before He Cheats.png\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Carrie Underwood]]\n| album      = [[Some Hearts]]\n| released   = August 19, 2006\n| format     = [[Music download|Digital download]]\n| recorded   = 2005\n| studio     = [[FAME Studios|FAME]], Muscle Shoals, Alabama\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Country music|Country]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mapes |first1=Jillian |last2=Tom |first2=Hawking|url=http://flavorwire.com/489397/25-of-musics-most-misandrist-anthems/view-all |title=25 of Music\u2019s Most Misandrist Anthems |publisher=Flavorwire |date=November 19, 2014 |accessdate=October 27, 2017}}</ref>\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=19}} {{small|(album version)}}\n| label      = [[Arista Records|Arista]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Josh Kear]]|[[Chris Tompkins]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/ascapcma/2007/song.html |title=2007 ASCAP Country Music Awards |publisher=Ascap.com |date=2007-10-15 |accessdate=2012-01-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080517021231/http://www.ascap.com/eventsawards/awards/ascapcma/2007/song.html |archivedate=2008-05-17 }}</ref>}}\n| producer   = [[Mark Bright (record producer)|Mark Bright]]\n| prev_title = [[Don't Forget to Remember Me]]\n| prev_year  = 2006\n| next_title = [[Wasted (Carrie Underwood song)|Wasted]]\n| next_year  = 2007\n| misc       = {{External music video|\"[http://www.cmt.com/videos/carrie-underwood/106496/before-he-cheats.jhtml Before He Cheats]\" at CMT.com}}\n}}\n\"'''Before He Cheats'''\" is a song written by [[Chris Tompkins]] and [[Josh Kear]] and the third wide-release single from [[Carrie Underwood]]'s debut studio album, ''[[Some Hearts]]'' (2005). It was the fifth release from the album overall. The song tells the story of a woman taking revenge on her potentially unfaithful boyfriend/husband.\n\nThe song became an enormous [[Crossover music|crossover]] success, topping the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Country Songs]] chart for five consecutive weeks, reaching the top five on the ''Billboard'' [[Adult Top 40]] chart, and becoming a top ten hit on the ''Billboard'' [[Mainstream Top 40]] and [[Adult Contemporary (chart)|Adult Contemporary]] charts. On the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart, \"Before He Cheats\" reached number eight and achieved a longevity of 64 consecutive weeks on the chart, making it the sixth longest-charting single in the history of the Hot 100 chart.\n\n\"Before He Cheats\" became the first ever country song to sell over two million digitally and was once the best-selling country song of all time.<ref name=\"billboard\"/> It had sold 4,483,000 digital downloads as of January 2020,<ref name=\"us sales\" /> and was once the best-selling song by an ''[[American Idol]]'' contestant but is now the third best-selling (behind [[Phillip Phillips]]' \"[[Home (Phillip Phillips song)|Home]]\" and [[Kelly Clarkson]]'s \"[[Stronger (What Doesn't Kill You)]]\").<ref name=\"Ask Billboard\">{{cite news|title=Ask Billboard: Disney's Biggest Billboard Hits |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/5885499/ask-billboard-disneys-biggest-billboard-hits?page=0%2C2 |last=Trust |first=Gary |work=Ask Billboard |publisher=Billboard |date=2014-01-28 |accessdate=January 29, 2014}}</ref> It has also been certified 5\u00d7 Platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]], Underwood's largest-selling single to date.<ref name=\"CarrieUnderwoodSSearch\">{{cite web |url=https://www.riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS&artist=Carrie%20Underwood&format=SINGLE&go=Search&perPage=50 |title=RIAA Gold and Platinum Search for singles by Carrie Underwood |publisher=Riaa.com |accessdate=2015-08-15 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130225031458/http://riaa.com/goldandplatinumdata.php?table=SEARCH_RESULTS |archivedate=2013-02-25 }}</ref>\n\nThe song has received a number of accolades. At the [[50th Annual Grammy Awards]], Underwood won the [[Grammy Award for Best Female Country Vocal Performance]] and the song's writers won the [[Grammy Award for Best Country Song]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cmt.com/news/country-music/1581299/vince-gill-wins-best-country-album-grammy.jhtml |title=Vince Gill Wins Best Country Album Grammy |date=February 11, 2008 |author =Calvin Gilbert |work=CMT News }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.grammy.com/artist/carrie-underwood |title=Carrie Underwood |publisher=Grammy }}</ref> It received a nomination for the [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year]] as well. It was also named the 2007 Single of the Year by the [[Country Music Association Awards]]. It ranked on CMT's ''40 Greatest Songs of the Decade'' at number 25, along with Underwood's other signature hit, \"[[Jesus, Take the Wheel]]\", which ranked number four.\n\n==Background==\n\"Before He Cheats\" tells the story of a woman taking revenge on her potentially unfaithful boyfriend or husband.\n\nShe imagines him hanging out and flirting with a \"bleach-blonde\" girl, shooting pool, buying her a [[alcoholic beverage|drink]], dancing, and hoping to \"[[sexual intercourse|get lucky]]\" with her. In retaliation, she vandalizes his customized [[four-wheel drive]] vehicle by [[Vandalism|keying]] the sides, carving her name into its leather seats, smashing the headlights with a [[Louisville Slugger]] baseball bat and slashing all four tires. All of these actions are part of her hopes that this will make him \"think before he cheats\" again.\n\nAlthough the song is about a tale of revenge, according to Carrie Underwood, while she had been cheated on before, \"I wouldn't recommend doing any property damage, though. I'm a 'let it go, move on' kind of person.\"<ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web |url= https://www.rollingstone.com/music/song-stories/before-he-cheats-carrie-underwood |title=Before He Cheats |work=Billboard }}</ref>\n\n\"Before He Cheats\" is set in the key of [[F-sharp minor]]. It has a moderate tempo in [[cut time]] with a \"shuffle\" beat. The song's main chord pattern is F{{sharp}}m-E-D{{sub|sus}}2-C{{sharp}}m, and Underwood's vocals range from F{{sharp}}3-C{{sharp}}5.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0136567|title='Before He Cheats' sheet music|work=musicnotes.com|accessdate=13 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video for \"Before He Cheats\" was directed by [[Roman White]].<ref name=\"cmtvideo\">{{cite web|title=Videos: Carrie Underwood, \"Before He Cheats\"|url=http://www.cmt.com/videos/carrie-underwood/106496/before-he-cheats.jhtml|work=CMT.com|accessdate=2008-02-15| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080205003936/http://www.cmt.com/videos/carrie-underwood/106496/before-he-cheats.jhtml| archivedate= 5 February 2008 | url-status= live}}</ref> In the beginning of the video Underwood is seen leaving a parking lot brandishing a Louisville Slugger, having just vandalized her husband/boyfriend's truck for cheating on her. In other scenes, the \"husband/boyfriend\" (portrayed by actor Tabb Shoup) is seen kissing another woman. As the video progresses Underwood takes the stage to sing as various objects behind her, such as lamps, are seen exploding. At one point, a screen shot of the front seat of the truck is seen with Underwood's name carved in it, which she mentions during the chorus of the song. Eventually, she catches up with her cheating husband/boyfriend with the other woman. After looking shocked for a second, she scoffs and drops the keys to his now-demolished truck into his drink. Towards the end Underwood struts down a street, singing along with the song, while different objects are shown flying across the air, glasses are seen shattering, and light bulbs explode, paying homage to [[Brian De Palma]]'s ''[[Carrie (1976 film)|Carrie]]''. At the very end of the music video, the truck is shown completely destroyed.\n\nThe early scenes in the video featuring a crowd in a narrow street and Underwood in a parking garage, were filmed in and around [[Printer's Alley]] in downtown [[Nashville, Tennessee]]. The final scene, featuring the exploding glass and light bulbs, was filmed on Fourth Avenue just north of Church Street in Nashville.\n\n\"Before He Cheats\" made [[Great American Country|GAC]] music video history by debuting at number one. It also marks the third consecutive number-one music video on GAC for Underwood. It made history on CMT's Top Twenty Countdown for being at number one for a consecutive five weeks. In December 2006, \"Before He Cheats\" was named the best video of 2006 by CMT's Top 20 Countdown. It also finished number two in GAC's Video of the Year for 2006 behind [[Trace Adkins]]'s \"[[Honky Tonk Badonkadonk]]\". Proving its crossover success, the video made a debut at number 15 on the ''[[VSpot Top 20 Countdown]]'', peaking at number 4.\n\nThe video premiered on [[MTV]]'s ''[[Total Request Live]]'' in April 2007, this is the second country music video to be premiered in this program, the first being \"[[These Boots Are Made for Walkin']]\" by [[Jessica Simpson]].\n\nOn April 16, 2007, the video for \"Before He Cheats\" swept the [[CMT Music Awards]], winning three categories: Video of the Year, Female Video of the Year, and Director of the Year. Underwood made history by being the first female to win Video of the Year.\n\nThe video also garnered Carrie a nomination for Music Video of the Year at the 2007 [[Country Music Association]] Awards and a nomination for a [[2007 MTV Video Music Awards|2007 MTV Video Music Award]] in the category of Best New Artist.\n\nDuring an ''[[NBC Sunday Night Football]]'' telecast of a [[Dallas Cowboys]]-[[New York Giants]] game, the song was played over the Dallas offensive line-up announcements after Underwood broke up with Dallas QB [[Tony Romo]].\n\nThe music video was ranked number nine on CMT's 100 Greatest Videos.<ref>{{cite web|title=100 Greatest Videos |url=http://lounge.teamshania.com/showthread.php?t=6760 |accessdate=2008-07-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081211161533/http://lounge.teamshania.com/showthread.php?t=6760 |archivedate=December 11, 2008 }}</ref>  It also ranked number one on [[Great American Country|GAC]]'s ''Top 50 Videos of the 2000s''.\n\nIn 2009, the music video for the song was voted number one by fans as VH1's Greatest Diva Music Video of all-time, before the airing of the annual VH1 Divas Live special.\n\n==Commercial performance==\n\"Before He Cheats\" first appeared on the charts in February 2006. Although it had not at that point been released as a single, many country stations began giving the song unsolicited airplay, leading it to debut on the ''Billboard'' [[Hot Country Songs]] chart at number 59. By the time the song was officially released as ''Some Hearts''&#39; third single in August of that year, it had already racked up 20 non-consecutive weeks on the chart, reaching as high as number 49. After the official release, the song climbed the country charts quickly, reaching number one in November and remaining there for five weeks. This was Underwood's third consecutive number one country single and fourth number one single overall. It also managed to debut on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart at number 92, and by November it had reached number 16 on that chart. By the end of 2006, the song began to slowly descend the charts, and it had appeared the single had peaked.\n\nHowever, pop radio began to take notice of the song in February 2007, around the time of Underwood's [[Grammy Award]] wins. As the single increased its top 40 airplay, it began to rebound on the Hot 100 chart. The new airplay, along with attention from numerous award show wins for the song, such as favorite country song at the 2007 [[People's Choice Awards]] in January and Video of the Year at the 2007 [[Country Music Television|CMT]]s in April, reinvigorated digital sales as well. When it finally peaked at number 8 in May 2007, it had already logged 38 weeks on the chart, making it the longest-trek to the top 10 ever. As pop airplay began dying down, the song got a third life on the [[adult contemporary]] format, which began playing the song in May. \"Before He Cheats\" spent 64 consecutive weeks on the Hot 100 chart, before finally falling off in late November 2007. The song is one of the longest-charting hits in ''Billboard'' history, and was the third longest-running hit of the 2000s decade.\n\n\"Before He Cheats\" was ranked sixth on the 2007 Hot 100 Year-end chart and fifth on the 2007 Hot 100 Airplay Year-end chart by ''Billboard''. It was also ranked tenth on the 2007 Adult Contemporary Year-end chart.\n\nThe song sold over two million in digital sales in December 2007, and was certified 2\u00d7 Platinum by the [[Recording Industry Association of America|RIAA]] in February 2008, making it the first country song to achieve this feat.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-maroon-5-beats-coldplay-211508183.html |title=Chart Watch: Maroon 5 Beats Coldplay |author= Paul Grein |work=Chart Watch (Yahoo Music) |date=June 25, 2014}}</ref> It was the best-selling single from an ''[[American Idol]]'' contestant until [[Kelly Clarkson]]'s \"[[Stronger (What Doesn't Kill You)]]\" surpassed it in the spring of 2012, and is still Underwood's best-selling single to date. It has sold over one million ringtones. In Canada, it is certified as Platinum. On August 10, 2015, the song was certified 5\u00d7 Platinum by the RIAA.{{Certification Cite Ref|region=United States|type=single|title=Before He Cheats|artist=Carrie Underwood}} Despite not charting in the United Kingdom, \"Before He Cheats\" received a Silver certification from the [[British Phonographic Industry]] in December 2018 for sales and streams exceeding 200,000; it is Underwood's only certified song in the UK.<ref name=\"ukcert\"/>\n\nThe song has sold 4,483,000 digital downloads in the United States as of January 2020,<ref name=\"us sales\">{{cite web |last=Bjorke |first=Matt |title=Top 30 Digital Country Songs Chart: January 7, 2020|url=http://roughstock.com/news/2020/01/44075-top-30-digital-country-songs-chart-january-7-2020 |work=Rough Stock |date=January 7, 2020 |accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref> and it is the third best-selling song by an ''[[American Idol]]'' contestant in the United States (behind [[Phillip Phillips]]' \"[[Home (Phillip Phillips song)|Home]]\" and [[Kelly Clarkson]]'s \"[[Stronger (What Doesn't Kill You)]]\").<ref name=\"Ask Billboard\"/> It is also the eighth best-selling country song in the US.<ref name=\"billboard jan 2014\">{{cite news |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/the-615/5862305/florida-georgia-line-cruise-sets-all-time-country-sales-record |title=Florida Georgia Line's 'Cruise' Sets All-Time Country Sales Record |author=Wade Jessen |date= January 6, 2014 |work=Billboard }}</ref>\n\nOn January 16, 2014, \"Before He Cheats\" entered the [[Irish Singles Chart]] at number 98, becoming Underwood's first appearance on that chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p/musicvideo/music/archive/index_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2014&year=2014&week=03|title=GFK Chart-Track|website=www.chart-track.co.uk|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn December 31, 2015, the song was performed live along with \"[[Smoke Break]]\" and \"[[Heartbeat (Carrie Underwood song)|Heartbeat]]\" on ''[[Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2015/12/31/carrie-underwood-new-years-performance-dick-clark-rockin-eve-medley-smoke-break-heatbeat/|title=Carrie Underwood Slays The Stage At New Year\u2019s Rockin\u2019 Eve With Amazing Medley|first=Emy|last=LaCroix|date=1 January 2016|publisher=|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref><ref>http://abc.go.com/shows/new-years-rockin-eve/news/performers/carrie-underwood-rocks-times-sqaure-with-a-little-help-from-nashville-160101{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n==Cover versions==\n*[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]] singer [[Joe (singer)|Joe]] performed a cover version of the song as a [[Pepsi]] Smash exclusive on [[Yahoo! Music]]. He changed the lyrics to fit a male's perspective and titled his version \"Before I Cheat\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://video.music.yahoo.com/up/music/music/?rn=1301797&vid=44151156 |title=Yahoo! Music Videos |publisher=Video.music.yahoo.com |date=2009-04-21 |accessdate=2012-06-13 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009015419/http://video.music.yahoo.com/up/music/music/?rn=1301797&vid=44151156 |archivedate=2007-10-09 }}</ref>\n*On the second annual ''[[Idol Gives Back]]'' special, [[Teri Hatcher]] and [[Band from TV]] covered the song. The performance takes place after a scene in which Hatcher's TV husband ([[James Denton (actor)|James Denton]]) fixes Underwood's sink prompting Hatcher to then \"steal her song\" because Underwood \"tried to steal her man.\"\n*In 2010, [[Adrianne Leon]] sang a cover version on the American soap opera ''[[General Hospital]]'' while portraying [[Brook Lynn Ashton]].\n*[[Jennifer Love Hewitt]] performed the song on the second episode of the first season of ''[[The Client List (TV series)|The Client List]]''.\n*In 2013, [[Sasha Allen]] performed the song in ''[[The Voice (U.S. TV series)|The Voice]]''.\n*On her 2014 debut album, [[Ana Gasteyer]] released a jazz cover of the song.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Im-Hip-Ana-Gasteyer/dp/B00ND1KU0I|title=Amazon.com: I'm Hip: Ana Gasteyer: MP3 Downloads|work=amazon.com}}</ref>\n*In the movie ''[[Pitch Perfect 2]]'', the song is performed during the Riff-off by [[the Barden Bellas]].\n\n==Other versions==\nAt the [[51st Annual Country Music Association Awards|2017 CMA Awards]], [[Brad Paisley]] and Underwood performed \"Before He [[Twitter|Tweets]]\", which made fun of [[Donald Trump|President Donald Trump]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.journalnow.com/news/nation_world/watch-trump-inspires-before-he-tweets-duet-by-paisley-and/article_e4e95f1e-96e9-5be7-8b20-4d64b91b2bf9.html|title=WATCH: Trump inspires 'Before He Tweets' duet by Paisley and Underwood at CMAs|agency=[[Associated Press]]|work=[[Winston-Salem Journal]]|date=2017-11-09|accessdate=2017-11-09}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n\n===50th Grammy Awards===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2008 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Grammy Award for Best Female Country Vocal Performance|Best Female Country Vocal Performance]] || {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2008 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Grammy Award for Best Country Song|Country Song of the Year]] || {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2008 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[Grammy Award for Song of the Year|Song of the Year]] || {{nom}}\n{{End}}\n\n===33rd People's Choice Awards===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Favorite Country Song || {{won}}\n{{End}}\n\n===2007 CMT Music Awards===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Video of the Year || {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Female Video of the Year || {{won}}\n{{End}}\n\n===2007 Academy of Country Music Awards===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Music Video of the Year || {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Song of the Year || {{nom}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Single of the Year || {{nom}}\n{{End}}\n\n===2007 MTV Video Music Awards===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Best New Artist || {{nom}}\n{{End}}\n\n===2007 Country Music Association Awards===\n{{Awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Single of the Year || {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007 || style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Before He Cheats\" || style=\"text-align:center;\"| Song of the Year || {{nom}}\n|-\n|