{"title_page": "Glen O'Dee Hospital", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name       = Glen O'Dee Hospital\n| Org/Group  = [[NHS Grampian]]\n| Image      =Glen O' Dee Hospital - geograph.org.uk - 59521.jpg\n| Width      =\n| Caption    = The original building\n| Logo       = <!-- optional -->\n| Location   = Banchory\n| Region     = Aberdeenshire\n| State      = Scotland\n| Country    = UK\n| HealthCare = NHS\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = [[Community hospital]]\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = No\n| Affiliation= <!-- University or Medical School -->\n| Beds       =\n| Founded    = 1900 \n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = [http://www.nhsgrampian.org/nhsgrampian/gra_display_simple_index.jsp?pContentID=4087&p_applic=CCC&p_service=Content.show& NHS Grampian - Glen O'Dee Hospital - Banchory]\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n| map_type   =Scotland Aberdeenshire\n| map_caption=Shown in Aberdeenshire\n| coordinates={{coord|57|3|40|N|2|31|11|W|region:GB_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n}}\n[[File:Glenodeeintcorridor.jpg|thumb|right|The original Glen O' Dee Hospital, nurses quarter internal corridor]]\n\n'''Glen O' Dee Hospital''' is situated in the west end of [[Banchory]], [[Aberdeenshire]], [[Scotland]]. It is a small [[community hospital]] that provides services for the population of [[Royal Deeside]] supported by local [[general practitioner|GP]]s. It is managed by [[NHS Grampian]].\n\n==History==\nThe original building was commissioned as a sanctuary for [[tuberculosis]] patients<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.banchorygrouppractice.co.uk/info.aspx?p=10 |title=Glen O'Dee hospital |publisher=Banchory Group Practice |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> and opened as Nordrach on Dee Hospital<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scottisharchitects.org.uk/building_full.php?id=201481 |title=Nordrach-on-Dee Hospital |publisher=Dictionary of Scottish Architects |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> in 1900.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nhsgrampian.org/nhsgrampian/gra_display_simple_index.jsp?pContentID=4087&p_applic=CCC&p_service=Content.show& |title=Community hospitals: Glen O' Dee Hospital - Banchory |publisher=[[NHS Grampian]] |date=8 March 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nWhen tuberculosis died down it served as a luxury hotel (when it became \"Glen O' Dee\"), but was taken over during the [[World War II|Second World War]] to serve as a billet for troops.<ref name=fire>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-north-east-orkney-shetland-37652859 |title=Historic Glen O'Dee hospital in Banchory destroyed by 'wilful' fire |work=BBC News |date=14 October 2016|accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref> In 1955 it became a convalescent hospital.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.scotsman.com/news/anger-as-a-listed-building-is-sold-for-luxury-flats-1-667431 |title=Anger as A-listed building is sold for luxury flats |work=[[The Scotsman]] |date=7 October 2003 |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> It reprised its role in contagious diseases when a [[typhoid]] epidemic hit nearby [[Aberdeen]] in the 1960s, but its last use was as a residential home for the elderly before it closed in 1998.<ref name=fire/>\n\nThe original building was featured on the [[BBC]]'s ''Restoration'' programme and, although local people compaigned to have it restored, it continued to sit empty and deteriorating.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-north-east-orkney-shetland-37676954|title=Boys aged 13 charged over Glen O'Dee hospital fire in Banchory|publisher=BBC|date=17 October 2016|accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref> The building was badly damaged by fire on 14 October 2016 with police treating the incident as wilful fire-raising.<ref name=fire/>\n\nA small modern community hospital staffed by [[General practitioner|GP]]s now operates on the site.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banchorygrouppractice.co.uk/info.aspx?p=10|title=Glen O'Dee Community Hospital|publisher=Banchory Group Practice|accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref> A befriending service was established at the community hospital in 2013 matching older patients ready to be discharged, but lacking confidence to return home, with a volunteer befriender. The volunteers then visit the older patients regularly in hospital and at home after discharge, offering on-going emotional and practical support.  Local GPs reported the service had improved the overall health and wellbeing of their patients and reduced the number of medically unnecessary GP visits.<ref>{{cite news|title=Befriending project helps older people after discharge|url=http://www.kincardineshireobserver.co.uk/news/local-headlines/befriending-project-helps-older-people-after-discharge-1-3797326|accessdate=25 June 2015|publisher=Kincardineshire Observer|date=10 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://entrezlecarnaval.f2s.com/photos/index.php/Hospitals%20&%20Asylums/Glen_O'_Dee_Hospital Pictures of the decaying interior of the original building]\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/131118269@N07/17370781731/ Aerial photo 1 of the derelict hospital taken in May 2015]\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/131118269@N07/17184952899/ Aerial photo 2 of the derelict hospital taken in May 2015]\n\n{{Social work}}\n{{Hospitals in NHS Grampian}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Glen Odee Hospital}}\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1900]]\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1998]]\n[[Category:NHS Grampian]]\n[[Category:NHS Scotland hospitals]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in Aberdeenshire]]\n[[Category:Category A listed buildings in Aberdeenshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name       = Glen O'Dee Hospital\n| Org/Group  = [[NHS Grampian]]\n| Image      =Glen O' Dee Hospital - geograph.org.uk - 59521.jpg\n| Width      =\n| Caption    = The original building\n| Logo       = <!-- optional -->\n| Location   = Banchory\n| Region     = Aberdeenshire\n| State      = Scotland\n| Country    = UK\n| HealthCare = NHS\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = [[Community hospital]]\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = No\n| Affiliation= <!-- University or Medical School -->\n| Beds       =\n| Founded    = 1900 \n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = [http://www.nhsgrampian.org/nhsgrampian/gra_display_simple_index.jsp?pContentID=4087&p_applic=CCC&p_service=Content.show& NHS Grampian - Glen O'Dee Hospital - Banchory]\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n| map_type   =Scotland Aberdeenshire\n| map_caption=Shown in Aberdeenshire\n| coordinates={{coord|57|3|40|N|2|31|11|W|region:GB_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}\n}}\n[[File:Glenodeeintcorridor.jpg|thumb|right|The original Glen O' Dee Hospital, nurses quarter internal corridor]]\n\n'''Glen O' Dee Hospital''' is situated in the west end of [[Banchory]], [[Aberdeenshire]], [[Scotland]]. It is a small [[community hospital]] that provides services for the population of [[Royal Deeside]] supported by local [[general practitioner|GP]]s. It is managed by [[NHS Grampian]].\n\n==History==\nThe original building was commissioned as a sanctuary for [[tuberculosis]] patients<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.banchorygrouppractice.co.uk/info.aspx?p=10 |title=Glen O'Dee hospital |publisher=Banchory Group Practice |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> and opened as Nordrach on Dee Hospital<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scottisharchitects.org.uk/building_full.php?id=201481 |title=Nordrach-on-Dee Hospital |publisher=Dictionary of Scottish Architects |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> in 1900.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nhsgrampian.org/nhsgrampian/gra_display_simple_index.jsp?pContentID=4087&p_applic=CCC&p_service=Content.show& |title=Community hospitals: Glen O' Dee Hospital - Banchory |publisher=[[NHS Grampian]] |date=8 March 2012 |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nWhen tuberculosis died down it served as a luxury hotel (when it became \"Glen O' Dee\"), but was taken over during the [[World War II|Second World War]] to serve as a billet for troops.<ref name=fire>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-north-east-orkney-shetland-37652859 |title=Historic Glen O'Dee hospital in Banchory destroyed by 'wilful' fire |work=BBC News |date=14 October 2016|accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref> In 1955 it became a convalescent hospital.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.scotsman.com/news/anger-as-a-listed-building-is-sold-for-luxury-flats-1-667431 |title=Anger as A-listed building is sold for luxury flats |work=[[The Scotsman]] |date=7 October 2003 |accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> It reprised its role in contagious diseases when a [[typhoid]] epidemic hit nearby [[Aberdeen]] in the 1960s, but its last use was as a residential home for the elderly before it closed in 1998.<ref name=fire/>\n\nThe original building was featured on the [[BBC]]'s ''Restoration'' programme and, although local people compaigned to have it restored, it continued to sit empty and deteriorating.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-north-east-orkney-shetland-37676954|title=Boys aged 13 charged over Glen O'Dee hospital fire in Banchory|publisher=BBC|date=17 October 2016|accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref> The building was badly damaged by fire on 14 October 2016 with police treating the incident as wilful fire-raising.<ref name=fire/>\n\nA small modern community hospital staffed by [[General practitioner|GP]]s now operates on the site.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.banchorygrouppractice.co.uk/info.aspx?p=10|title=Glen O'Dee Community Hospital|publisher=Banchory Group Practice|accessdate=30 December 2018}}</ref> A befriending service was established at the community hospital in 2013 matching older patients ready to be discharged, but lacking confidence to return home, with a volunteer befriender. The volunteers then visit the older patients regularly in hospital and at home after discharge, offering on-going emotional and practical support.  Local GPs reported the service had improved the overall health and wellbeing of their patients and reduced the number of medically unnecessary GP visits.<ref>{{cite news|title=Befriending project helps older people after discharge|url=http://www.kincardineshireobserver.co.uk/news/local-headlines/befriending-project-helps-older-people-after-discharge-1-3797326|accessdate=25 June 2015|publisher=Kincardineshire Observer|date=10 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://entrezlecarnaval.f2s.com/photos/index.php/Hospitals%20&%20Asylums/Glen_O'_Dee_Hospital Pictures of the decaying interior of the original building]\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/131118269@N07/17370781731/ Aerial photo 1 of the derelict hospital taken in May 2015]\n* [https://www.flickr.com/photos/131118269@N07/17184952899/ Aerial photo 2 of the derelict hospital taken in May 2015]\n\n{{Social work}}\n{{Hospitals in NHS Grampian}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Glen Odee Hospital}}\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1900]]\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1998]]\n[[Category:NHS Grampian]]\n[[Category:NHS Scotland hospitals]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in Aberdeenshire]]\n[[Category:Category A listed buildings in Aberdeenshire]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glen_O%27Dee_Hospital"}
{"title_page": "Helena Douglas", "text_new": "{{Infobox video game character\n|image = [[File:Helena DOA6.png|150px]]\n|caption = Helena Douglas in ''Dead or Alive 6''\n|series = [[Dead or Alive (series)|Dead or Alive]]\n|firstgame = ''[[Dead or Alive 2]]'' (1999)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.ign.com/characters/helena-douglas |archive-url=https://archive.today/20141019193527/http://uk.ign.com/characters/helena-douglas |url-status=dead |archive-date=2014-10-19 |title=Helena Douglas - IGN |publisher=Uk.ign.com |date=2006-11-21 |accessdate=2014-10-19 }}</ref>\n|creator = [[Tomonobu Itagaki]]\n|voice = {{Ubl|'''English'''|[[Karen Strassman]] (''DOAX2''\u2013''DOA Paradise'',<ref name=\"btva\">{{cite web |title=Helena Douglas Voice - Dead or Alive franchise |url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/characters/Dead-or-Alive/Helena-Douglas/ |website=Behind The Voice Actors |accessdate=19 December 2019|postscript=. A green check mark indicates that the role has been confirmed using a screenshot (or collage of screenshots) of the title's list of voice actors and their respective characters found in its closing credits and/or other reliable sources of information.}}</ref> ''DOA5''-present<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/KarenStrassman/status/1067040844761505797 |title=Delighted to be back as Helena!! |publisher=Twitter |date= |accessdate=2018-12-01}}</ref>)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.otakuthon.com/2016/guests/goh/ |title=Guests of Honour - Otakuthon 2016 |publisher=Otakuthon.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-29}}</ref><br/>[[Julianne Buescher]] (''DOA Dimensions'')<ref name=\"btva\"/>|'''Japanese'''|[[:jp:\u5c0f\u5c71\u88d5\u9999|Yuka Koyama]]<ref name=\"btva\"/>}}\n|portrayer = [[Sarah Carter]] (film)\n|motion_actor = \n|origin = [[France]]\n|nationality = [[French people|French]]\n|occupation = Opera singer (''DOA2'')<ref name=ign>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2006/11/21/videogame-babe-of-the-day-helena |title=Videogame Babe of the Day: Helena - IGN |publisher=www.ign.com |date= 2006-11-21 |accessdate=2014-10-19}}</ref> <br/> President and CEO of DOATEC (''DOA4''\u2013present)\n|fighting_style = [[Piguaquan]]\n}}\n'''Helena Douglas''' (\u30a8\u30ec\u30ca\u30fb\u30c0\u30b0\u30e9\u30b9 ''Erena Dagurasu?'') is a [[player character]] in the ''[[Dead or Alive (series)|Dead or Alive]]'' series of [[fighting game]]s by [[Team Ninja]] and [[Koei Tecmo]]. She was introduced in 1999's ''[[Dead or Alive 2]]'' as a French opera singer seeking to avenge her mother's murder. Due to her blood relation to [[Fame Douglas]], the original head of the antagonistic organization behind the ''Dead or Alive'' fighting tournaments, she has become a key character in the franchise, including serving as the [[protagonist]] of ''[[Dead or Alive 4]]''.\n\n==Appearances==\n===In video games===\n{{update section|date=March 2019}}\n\nHelena Douglas is the [[Legitimacy (family law)|illegitimate]] daughter of [[Fame Douglas]] and his [[Mistress (lover)|mistress]], a French [[soprano]] named Maria. Seemingly distant from her father, Helena was hardly affected by his assassination after the first Dead or Alive, and instead followed in her mother's footsteps by becoming a successful opera singer in her own right. However, she herself is targeted in an attempted [[Contract killing|hit]] during one of her performances, but Maria spots the assassin's sniper rifle at the last second and intentionally takes the fatal bullet intended for her daughter, leaving Helena alone and seeking vengeance.\n\nShe officially debuts in ''[[Dead or Alive 2]]'' (1999), where, while searching for the killer, she discovers that her parents' deaths and the attempt on her own life are connected to the Dead or Alive (DOA) World Combat Championship, and enters the tournament to discover the truth. Although never explained in the series, Helena appears to have learned or known information pertaining to the Dead or Alive Tournament Executive Committee (DOATEC), especially after encountering an amnesiac contestant named [[Hayate (Dead or Alive)|Hayate]]. Helena implicates [[Ayane (Dead or Alive)|Ayane]] as her mother's assassin, an accusation Ayane neither confirms nor denies, which causes a fight to break out between them.\n\nHelena returns for ''[[Dead or Alive 3]]'' (2001), and is captured by antagonist [[Victor Donovan]] and imprisoned.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gantayat |first=Anoop |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2005/12/02/dead-or-alive-4-the-characters |title=Dead or Alive 4: The Characters - IGN |work=uk.ign.com |date=2005-12-02 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> Although Helena insists that she has no ties to DOATEC, Donovan declares that her freedom and the revelation of the truth behind DOATEC\u2014her father having been the head of the organization prior to his death\u2014hinges on her winning the third tournament. In the meantime, Donovan assigns [[Christie (Dead or Alive)|Christie]] to keep an eye on her, with orders to kill her if necessary. However, when confronted by Helena, Christie admits that she is an assassin sent to terminate her.\n\nHelena takes over as new chairperson of DOATEC in 2005's ''[[Dead or Alive 4]]'', in which she is the [[main protagonist]]. She hires the assassin [[Bayman]] to take out Donovan, a job he declines. When the DOATEC Tritower comes under attack by the Mugen Tenshin ninja clan, Helena meets [[Lisa Hamilton|Lisa]], who admits she tricked the clan into attacking in order to stop Donovan. She later discovers that she and [[Kokoro (Dead or Alive)|Kokoro]] are blood-related, as her mother Miyako had been one of Fame Douglas' mistresses. Helena learns the truth about Christie and they meet in battle, the result of which is unknown, save for the fact that they both survive. In her arcade ending, Helena elects to go down with DOATEC by activating the building's self-destruct mechanism.\n\nIn ''[[Dead or Alive 5]]'' (2012), a distressed Helena reflects on the deaths of Maria and another of her father's past lovers, Anna. As Ayane, Hayate, and [[Ryu Hayabusa]] are detonating the DOATEC headquarters, Helena elects to give up her life in the flames of the wreckage before [[Zack (Dead or Alive)|Zack]] arrives in a helicopter to rescue her. With Zack's help,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gamesurf.tiscali.it/news/trama-e-foto-per-dead-or-alive-5-c44114.html |title=Trama e foto per Dead or Alive 5 - Gamesurf.it |website=Gamesurf.tiscali.it |date= |accessdate=2016-02-06}}</ref> she becomes the leader of the newly reformed DOATEC and announces the revival of the ''Dead or Alive'' tournaments,<ref name=\"siliconera\">{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2012/08/11/team-ninjas-dead-or-alive-5-chart-shows-character-relationships/|title=Team Ninja's ''Dead or Alive 5'' Chart Shows Character Relationships|first=Ishaan|last=Sahdev|work=Siliconera.com|date= August 11, 2012|accessdate=January 28, 2016}}</ref> then enlists Hayate and Ayane to help [[Kasumi (Dead or Alive)|Kasumi]] on the latter's mission of destroying an army of evil clones of herself, though Helena was unaware that Kasumi she saw was actually a clone, until the real Kasumi joins the fray in the final battle.\n\n''[[Dead or Alive 5 Ultimate]]'' introduced Helena's loyal maid servant [[Marie Rose (Dead or Alive)|Marie Rose]], whom Helena send her to keep an eye on a young scholar fighter who was introduced in ''[[Dead or Alive 5 Last Round]]'' named Honoka in ''[[Dead or Alive 6]]'', realizing that MIST will kidnap her upon witnessing a familiar phenomenal power within Honoka in the day when the said young fighter was disqualified in the fifth tournament\u2019s Asian qualifier match. As Hayate met [[Rig (Dead or Alive)|Rig]] shortly at the night after the fifth tournament ended in the same time Helena set self-destruct DiG where MIST been hiding, but not in another way it seems, Helena realize something tragically happened to Rig, not even Rig aware what happened after his \u201chome\u201d was destroyed and begin to live at [[Bass Armstrong]]\u2019s apartment in New York. Although Lisa manage to survive the explosion at MIST\u2019s first hideout on DiG, Helena tried to object Lisa from keeping herself take a risk to end Donovan\u2019s terror, but realize the latter has a point on not wasting time to let a madman like Donovan get away from his crimes. When Kokoro found out her connection with their late-biological father Fame, Helena got into an argument with her half-sister over their illegitimate family, until Zack manage to calm down the situation, much to Helena\u2019s relieve. As Marie, Bayman and the ninjas finally found MIST\u2019s second hideout in the same time after Honoka and Ayane\u2019s biological evil father [[Raidou (Dead or Alive)|Raidou]] was revived as an undead cyber nukenin, Helena confronts the young scientist who led a resurrection project behind Raidou\u2019s revival, NiCO, who also revived Helena\u2019s late-mother Maria off-screen. Upon realizing what NiCO\u2019s plan is, Helena disapproves of bringing their lost parents back to life, citing that one needs to move on and vowing that NiCO will someday learn to move on from her pain as Helena has.\n\nHelena is playable in the spinoff games ''[[Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball]]'' (2003), ''[[Dead or Alive Xtreme 2]]'' (2006) and ''[[Dead or Alive Paradise]]'' (2010), still pursuing Christie. She returned as one of nine player characters in the 2016 release ''[[Dead or Alive Xtreme 3]]'' after being voted onto the roster in a Japanese fan poll.<ref name=\"gamecity\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/9/19/9356129/dead-or-alive-xtreme-3-release-date-playstation-vr|title=Dead or Alive Xtreme 3 launches spring 2016 with PlayStation VR support|first=Michael|last=McWhertor|work=Polygon.com|date=September 19, 2015|accessdate=January 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Design and gameplay====\n[[File:DOA Helena concepts.png|thumb|250px|Two stages of brainstorming a \"female piguaquan\" Helena prototype for ''DOA2''|alt=|left]]\n\nHelena is listed as standing 5'7\" in height and 108 pounds,<ref name=\"dm\"/> with long blonde hair and aqua green eyes, while her measurements are 35-22-34.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/dead-or-alive-xtreme-beach-volleyball/guide/page_5.html |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball - xbox\u2014Walkthrough and Guide - Page 5 - GameSpy |work=Xbox.gamespy.com |date=2003-01-03 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Carle |first=Chris |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2006/11/21/videogame-babe-of-the-day-helena |title=Videogame Babe of the Day: Helena|work=uk.ign.com |date=2006-11-21 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> [[Pre-order]] bonuses for ''[[Dead or Alive 5 Last Round]]'' offered by [[Amazon.com]] included a downloadable operatic \"Showstopper\" costume for the character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gameplorer.de/dead-or-alive-5-last-round-release-datum-next-gen/|title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round: Release-Datum f\u00fcr PS4 und Xbox One + Vorbesteller-Boni enth\u00fcllt|work=Gameplorer.de|date=October 24, 2014|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/dead_or_alive_5_last_round/b/playstation4/archive/2014/10/23/dead-or-alive-5-last-round-coming-february-with-free-trials-in-tow.aspx|title=Dead Or Alive 5: Last Round Coming February With Free Trials In Tow|work=GameInformer.com|first=Mike|last= Futter|date=October 23, 2014}}</ref> One of Helena's outfits in ''Last Round'' is a dress designed by manga artist [[Tamiki Wakaki]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7n7A0HG9s48 |title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round\u2014Tamiki Wakaki Costumes |work=YouTube |date=2015-07-22 |accessdate=2015-09-25}}</ref> while others include downloadable costumes of Reina from ''[[Deception IV: The Nightmare Princess]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/teamninjastudio/status/614040395450748929 |title=Team NINJA on Twitter: \"Helena is Reina, the Princess of Tragedy|work=Twitter.com |date=2015-06-25 |accessdate=2015-09-25}}</ref> Vita Clotilde from [[Nihon Falcom]]'s ''[[The Legend of Heroes: Trails of Cold Steel]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pushsquare.com/news/2015/09/store_update_15th_september_2015_north_america |title=Store Update: 15th September 2015 (North America) |work=Push Square |date= |accessdate=2015-09-25}}</ref> Professor Tierra from [[Square Enix]]'s ''School Girl Strikers'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pushsquare.com/news/2015/11/transforming_schoolgirls_strike_dead_or_alive_5_with_new_costume_crossover |title=Transforming Schoolgirls Strike Dead or Alive 5 with New Costume Crossover |publisher=Push Square |date= |accessdate=2016-01-01}}</ref> and Aquarius from the manga and anime ''[[Fairy Tale]]'',<ref>{{cite web|author=By Sato|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2016/06/09/dead-alive-5-last-round-getting-fairy-tail-collaboration-costumes/ |title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round Is Getting Fairy Tail Collaboration Costumes |publisher=Siliconera |date=2016-06-09 |accessdate=2016-08-29}}</ref> as well as a  ninja outfit<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-newshub.com/gaming/ninja-clan-2-costume-pack-available-for-dead-or-alive-5-last-round |title=The real free press |publisher=The-newshub.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921115042/https://www.the-newshub.com/gaming/ninja-clan-2-costume-pack-available-for-dead-or-alive-5-last-round |archive-date=2016-09-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the Garrison Regiment uniform from ''[[Attack on Titan]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gematsu.com/2016/07/dead-alive-5-last-round-add-king-fighters-mai-shiranui-via-paid-dlc-september |title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round to add The King of Fighters' Mai Shiranui via paid DLC in September |publisher=Gematsu |date= |accessdate=2016-08-29}}</ref>\n\nAccording to [[IGN]], \"as one of the most technical characters in\" ''Dead or Alive 3'', \"Helena has a truckload of different special techniques and arguably the most powerful punch attacks in the game.\"<ref name=ign2>{{cite web|last=Chau |first=Anthony |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2001/11/15/doa-3-fighter-of-the-day-helena |title=DOA 3 Fighter Of The Day: Helena - IGN |work=uk.ign.com |date=2001-11-15 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> The site added that  her \"fluid motions make her the most graceful fighter\" in the series, and in ''[[Dead or Alive Ultimate]]'', Helena is a \"great mixture of leg and fist strength\" and is \"not the easiest character to master, but when you do master her techniques, you'll dominate.\"<ref name=ign3/> Hardcore Gaming 101 said, \"Her martial arts style, [[Pi Gua Quan]], is not often seen in fighting games, [and] relies on long-hauling circular movements to gain momentum.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/doa/doa.htm|title=Hardcore Gaming 101: Dead or Alive|author=Kurt Kalata and Sam Derboo|work=Hardcore Gaming 101|date=September 3, 2015|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref> Helena is an [[Unlockable (gaming)|unlockable]] character in ''Dead or Alive 4'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox360.gamespy.com/xbox-360/dead-or-alive-4/guide/page_6.html |title=Dead or Alive 4 - xbox360 - Walkthrough and Guide - Page 6 - GameSpy |work=Xbox360.gamespy.com |date=2006-01-24 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> in which she has many \"good 'launcher' attacks\" that can lead into [[Combo (video gaming)|juggle combo]]s, according to [[GameSpy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/dead-or-alive-ultimate/guide/page_24.html |title=''Dead or Alive Ultimate'' Walkthrough and Guide - Page 24 - GameSpy |work=Xbox.gamespy.com |date=2004-01-24 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref>\n\n===In film===\nHelena is a main character in the 2006 live-action film ''[[DOA: Dead or Alive]]'', played by [[Sarah Carter]]. Helena's role of tournament hostess remains intact, but her backstory is ignored and she is given an upbeat personality that contrasts to her aloof in-game disposition; she appears in one scene wearing roller skates, and a line of dialogue has her commenting about wanting to visit Paris. Throughout the movie, Helena is treated as a necessary annoyance by tournament organizer Donovan ([[Eric Roberts]]), who has gained control of DOATEC after the death of Helena's father. She additionally gains a noncanonical love interest in Donovan's technical assistant, Weatherby.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2007/06/15/doa-dead-or-alive|title=DOA: Dead or Alive|author=Stax (Jim Vejvoda)|work=IGN.com|date=June 15, 2007|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n[[File:C2E2 2014 Contest - Helena Douglas (14109313304).jpg|thumb|upright|Noelle d'Arda cosplaying Helena at the [[Chicago Comic & Entertainment Expo|C2E2]] 2014]]\n\nHelena has received mostly positive critical and public reception. Hilary Goldstein of IGN enthused in 2004, \"We love Helena because she's the default ass-kicker. Plus, her home arena, the burning Opera House, is among the coolest in ''DOA Ultimate''. Helena is also the only girl [in the series] that has classic beauty to her. The others play on that Asian school girl vibe men love, but Helena has more class (and bosom, sure) going for her ... the lack of [[slut]] outfits makes her the best dressed.\"<ref name=ign3>{{cite web|last=Goldstein |first=Hilary |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2004/09/22/girls-of-doau-helena |title=Girls of DOAU: Helena - IGN |publisher=Uk.ign.com |date=2004-09-22 |accessdate=2015-07-01}}</ref> The site further described Helena as \"gorgeous\" and a \"classy French vixen\".<ref name=ign/><ref name=ign2/> ''Official Dreamcast Magazine'' commented that Helena proved the stereotype of the \"fat opera chick\" to be \"wildly inaccurate.\"<ref name=dm>\"Alive & Heaving\". ''Dreamcast Magazine'' issue 5, page 39.</ref> [[GameFront]] included her among the top video game girls of all time in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.gamefront.com/top-video-game-girls-of-all-time/ |title=Top Video Game Girls of All Time |work=GameFront |date=2007-05-16 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> In 2014, Brazilian site [[GameHall]]'s \"Portal PlayGame\" ranked Helena as the eleventh-most sexy female video character, deeming her the \"most beautiful\" overall in the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://portalplaygame.com/top-100-as-personagens-mais-gatas-dos-games/ |title=TOP 100 \u2013 As Personagens mais gatas dos games &#124; Portal Play Game |publisher=Web.archive.org |date=2015-01-23 |accessdate=2015-07-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150123234148/http://portalplaygame.com/top-100-as-personagens-mais-gatas-dos-games/ |archivedate=January 23, 2015 }}</ref> Helena was voted the ''DOA'' series' tenth-most popular character in a fan poll conducted by Koei Tecmo in 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamecity.ne.jp/doa5/lastround/vote/index.html|title=DEAD OR ALIVE 5 Last Round ?|publisher=Gamecity.ne.jp|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> but while she was one of the characters voted by fans to qualify for ''Dead or Alive 3 Xtreme,'' she finished last (ninth) with the fewest percentage of votes.<ref name=\"gamecity\">{{cite web|title=\"DOAX3\"|url=https://www.gamecity.ne.jp/doax3/vote_result.html|website=Gamecity.ne.jp|accessdate=2015-09-19}}</ref>\n\n[[Joystiq]]'s Ludwig Kietzmann questioned \"the practices of Helena Douglas, a supposedly French CEO who dresses for sultry cabaret and literally beats up her employees.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Kietzmann |first=Ludwig |url=http://www.joystiq.com/2012/09/27/dead-or-alive-5-review/ |title=Dead or Alive 5 review: Begrudge match |publisher=Joystiq.com |date=2012-09-27 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> AJ Glasser of [[Kotaku]] declared Maria the \"best mom\" in fighting games, \"because nothing says 'Mommy loves you' like taking a sniper's bullet to the heart.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5238770/mommy-dearest-the-best-and-worst-mothers-in-video-games|title=Mommy Dearest: The Best and Worst Mothers in Video Games|first=AJ|last=Glasser|work=Kotaku.com|date=May 6, 2009|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref> However, the site included Fame Douglas among the worst fathers in video games. \"Fame knocks up a world-famous opera singer and then doesn't marry her; but he does leave his daughter his effed up company, DOATEC, after being assassinated. Thanks, Daddy!\"<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://kotaku.com/5297186/father-knows-best-the-best-and-worst-fathers-in-video-games |title=Father Knows Best: The Best and Worst Fathers in Video Games |first=AJ|last=Glasser|work=Kotaku.com |date=June 21, 2009|accessdate=June 18, 2015}}</ref> Helena was named one of the top seven \"hottest girls\" in video game film adaptations by Spanish magazine ''Marca Player'' in 2009.<ref>''Marca Player'' issue 9 page 50.</ref> Her fight scene with Christie placed eleventh in the 2012 \"best cinematic girl-on-girl fights\" online poll conducted by [[JoBlo.com]].<ref>{{cite web|author= Droz (Kevin Blanchard)|url=http://www.joblo.com/hollywood-celebrities/gossip/13115/results |title=HOTTIE POLL: What's the best cinematic girl-on-girl fight? |work=Joblo.com |date=2012-08-04 |accessdate=2016-02-06}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Dead or Alive characters|List of ''Dead or Alive'' characters]] {{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://teamninja-studio.com/doa5/uk/chara19.html}} (''DOA5'')\n\n{{Dead or Alive series}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Fictional businesspeople in video games]]\n[[Category:Characters created by Tomonobu Itagaki]]\n[[Category:Dead or Alive (franchise) characters]]\n[[Category:Female characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional business executives]]\n[[Category:Fictional French people in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional female musicians]]\n[[Category:Fictional Piguaquan practitioners]]\n[[Category:Fictional opera singers]]\n[[Category:Musician characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Singer characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Video game characters in film]]\n[[Category:Video game characters introduced in 1999]]\n[[Category:Video game protagonists]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox video game character\n|image = [[File:Helena DOA6.png|150px]]\n|caption = Helena Douglas in ''Dead or Alive 5 Infinite''\n|series = [[Dead or Alive (series)|Dead or Alive]]\n|firstgame = ''[[Dead or Alive 2]]'' (1999)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uk.ign.com/characters/helena-douglas |archive-url=https://archive.today/20141019193527/http://uk.ign.com/characters/helena-douglas |url-status=dead |archive-date=2014-10-19 |title=Helena Douglas - IGN |publisher=Uk.ign.com |date=2006-11-21 |accessdate=2014-10-19 }}</ref>\n|creator = [[Tomonobu Itagaki]]\n|voice = {{Ubl|'''English'''|[[Karen Strassman]] (''DOAX2''\u2013''DOA Paradise'',<ref name=\"btva\">{{cite web |title=Helena Douglas Voice - Dead or Alive franchise |url=https://www.behindthevoiceactors.com/characters/Dead-or-Alive/Helena-Douglas/ |website=Behind The Voice Actors |accessdate=19 December 2019|postscript=. A green check mark indicates that the role has been confirmed using a screenshot (or collage of screenshots) of the title's list of voice actors and their respective characters found in its closing credits and/or other reliable sources of information.}}</ref> ''DOA5''-present<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/KarenStrassman/status/1067040844761505797 |title=Delighted to be back as Helena!! |publisher=Twitter |date= |accessdate=2018-12-01}}</ref>)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.otakuthon.com/2016/guests/goh/ |title=Guests of Honour - Otakuthon 2016 |publisher=Otakuthon.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-29}}</ref><br/>[[Julianne Buescher]] (''DOA Dimensions'')<ref name=\"btva\"/>|'''Japanese'''|[[:jp:\u5c0f\u5c71\u88d5\u9999|Yuka Koyama]]<ref name=\"btva\"/>}}\n|portrayer = [[Sarah Carter]] (film)\n|motion_actor = \n|origin = [[France]]\n|nationality = [[French people|French]]\n|occupation = Opera singer (''DOA2'')<ref name=ign>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2006/11/21/videogame-babe-of-the-day-helena |title=Videogame Babe of the Day: Helena - IGN |publisher=www.ign.com |date= 2006-11-21 |accessdate=2014-10-19}}</ref> <br/> President and CEO of DOATEC (''DOA4''\u2013present)\n|fighting_style = [[Piguaquan]]\n}}\n'''Helena Douglas''' (\u30a8\u30ec\u30ca\u30fb\u30c0\u30b0\u30e9\u30b9 ''Erena Dagurasu?'') is a [[player character]] in the ''[[Dead or Alive (series)|Dead or Alive]]'' series of [[fighting game]]s by [[Team Ninja]] and [[Koei Tecmo]]. She was introduced in 1999's ''[[Dead or Alive 2]]'' as a French opera singer seeking to avenge her mother's murder. Due to her blood relation to [[Fame Douglas]], the original head of the antagonistic organization behind the ''Dead or Alive'' fighting tournaments, she has become a key character in the franchise, including serving as the [[protagonist]] of ''[[Dead or Alive 4]]''.\n\n==Appearances==\n===In video games===\n{{update section|date=March 2019}}\n\nHelena Douglas is the [[Legitimacy (family law)|illegitimate]] daughter of [[Fame Douglas]] and his [[Mistress (lover)|mistress]], a French [[soprano]] named Maria. Seemingly distant from her father, Helena was hardly affected by his assassination after the first Dead or Alive, and instead followed in her mother's footsteps by becoming a successful opera singer in her own right. However, she herself is targeted in an attempted [[Contract killing|hit]] during one of her performances, but Maria spots the assassin's sniper rifle at the last second and intentionally takes the fatal bullet intended for her daughter, leaving Helena alone and seeking vengeance.\n\nShe officially debuts in ''[[Dead or Alive 2]]'' (1999), where, while searching for the killer, she discovers that her parents' deaths and the attempt on her own life are connected to the Dead or Alive (DOA) World Combat Championship, and enters the tournament to discover the truth. Although never explained in the series, Helena appears to have learned or known information pertaining to the Dead or Alive Tournament Executive Committee (DOATEC), especially after encountering an amnesiac contestant named [[Hayate (Dead or Alive)|Hayate]]. Helena implicates [[Ayane (Dead or Alive)|Ayane]] as her mother's assassin, an accusation Ayane neither confirms nor denies, which causes a fight to break out between them.\n\nHelena returns for ''[[Dead or Alive 3]]'' (2001), and is captured by antagonist [[Victor Donovan]] and imprisoned.<ref>{{cite web|last=Gantayat |first=Anoop |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2005/12/02/dead-or-alive-4-the-characters |title=Dead or Alive 4: The Characters - IGN |work=uk.ign.com |date=2005-12-02 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> Although Helena insists that she has no ties to DOATEC, Donovan declares that her freedom and the revelation of the truth behind DOATEC\u2014her father having been the head of the organization prior to his death\u2014hinges on her winning the third tournament. In the meantime, Donovan assigns [[Christie (Dead or Alive)|Christie]] to keep an eye on her, with orders to kill her if necessary. However, when confronted by Helena, Christie admits that she is an assassin sent to terminate her.\n\nHelena takes over as new chairperson of DOATEC in 2005's ''[[Dead or Alive 4]]'', in which she is the [[main protagonist]]. She hires the assassin [[Bayman]] to take out Donovan, a job he declines. When the DOATEC Tritower comes under attack by the Mugen Tenshin ninja clan, Helena meets [[Lisa Hamilton|Lisa]], who admits she tricked the clan into attacking in order to stop Donovan. She later discovers that she and [[Kokoro (Dead or Alive)|Kokoro]] are blood-related, as her mother Miyako had been one of Fame Douglas' mistresses. Helena learns the truth about Christie and they meet in battle, the result of which is unknown, save for the fact that they both survive. In her arcade ending, Helena elects to go down with DOATEC by activating the building's self-destruct mechanism.\n\nIn ''[[Dead or Alive 5]]'' (2012), a distressed Helena reflects on the deaths of Maria and another of her father's past lovers, Anna. As Ayane, Hayate, and [[Ryu Hayabusa]] are detonating the DOATEC headquarters, Helena elects to give up her life in the flames of the wreckage before [[Zack (Dead or Alive)|Zack]] arrives in a helicopter to rescue her. With Zack's help,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gamesurf.tiscali.it/news/trama-e-foto-per-dead-or-alive-5-c44114.html |title=Trama e foto per Dead or Alive 5 - Gamesurf.it |website=Gamesurf.tiscali.it |date= |accessdate=2016-02-06}}</ref> she becomes the leader of the newly reformed DOATEC and announces the revival of the ''Dead or Alive'' tournaments,<ref name=\"siliconera\">{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2012/08/11/team-ninjas-dead-or-alive-5-chart-shows-character-relationships/|title=Team Ninja's ''Dead or Alive 5'' Chart Shows Character Relationships|first=Ishaan|last=Sahdev|work=Siliconera.com|date= August 11, 2012|accessdate=January 28, 2016}}</ref> then enlists Hayate and Ayane to help [[Kasumi (Dead or Alive)|Kasumi]] on the latter's mission of destroying an army of evil clones of herself, though Helena was unaware that Kasumi she saw was actually a clone, until the real Kasumi joins the fray in the final battle.\n\n''[[Dead or Alive 5 Ultimate]]'' introduced Helena's loyal maid servant [[Marie Rose (Dead or Alive)|Marie Rose]], whom Helena send her to keep an eye on a young scholar fighter who was introduced in ''[[Dead or Alive 5 Last Round]]'' named Honoka in ''[[Dead or Alive 6]]'', realizing that MIST will kidnap her upon witnessing a familiar phenomenal power within Honoka in the day when the said young fighter was disqualified in the fifth tournament\u2019s Asian qualifier match. As Hayate met [[Rig (Dead or Alive)|Rig]] shortly at the night after the fifth tournament ended in the same time Helena set self-destruct DiG where MIST been hiding, but not in another way it seems, Helena realize something tragically happened to Rig, not even Rig aware what happened after his \u201chome\u201d was destroyed and begin to live at [[Bass Armstrong]]\u2019s apartment in New York. Although Lisa manage to survive the explosion at MIST\u2019s first hideout on DiG, Helena tried to object Lisa from keeping herself take a risk to end Donovan\u2019s terror, but realize the latter has a point on not wasting time to let a madman like Donovan get away from his crimes. When Kokoro found out her connection with their late-biological father Fame, Helena got into an argument with her half-sister over their illegitimate family, until Zack manage to calm down the situation, much to Helena\u2019s relieve. As Marie, Bayman and the ninjas finally found MIST\u2019s second hideout in the same time after Honoka and Ayane\u2019s biological evil father [[Raidou (Dead or Alive)|Raidou]] was revived as an undead cyber nukenin, Helena confronts the young scientist who led a resurrection project behind Raidou\u2019s revival, NiCO, who also revived Helena\u2019s late-mother Maria off-screen. Upon realizing what NiCO\u2019s plan is, Helena disapproves of bringing their lost parents back to life, citing that one needs to move on and vowing that NiCO will someday learn to move on from her pain as Helena has.\n\nHelena is playable in the spinoff games ''[[Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball]]'' (2003), ''[[Dead or Alive Xtreme 2]]'' (2006) and ''[[Dead or Alive Paradise]]'' (2010), still pursuing Christie. She returned as one of nine player characters in the 2016 release ''[[Dead or Alive Xtreme 3]]'' after being voted onto the roster in a Japanese fan poll.<ref name=\"gamecity\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/9/19/9356129/dead-or-alive-xtreme-3-release-date-playstation-vr|title=Dead or Alive Xtreme 3 launches spring 2016 with PlayStation VR support|first=Michael|last=McWhertor|work=Polygon.com|date=September 19, 2015|accessdate=January 25, 2016}}</ref>\n\n====Design and gameplay====\n[[File:DOA Helena concepts.png|thumb|250px|Two stages of brainstorming a \"female piguaquan\" Helena prototype for ''DOA2''|alt=|left]]\n\nHelena is listed as standing 5'7\" in height and 108 pounds,<ref name=\"dm\"/> with long blonde hair and aqua green eyes, while her measurements are 35-22-34.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/dead-or-alive-xtreme-beach-volleyball/guide/page_5.html |title=Dead or Alive Xtreme Beach Volleyball - xbox\u2014Walkthrough and Guide - Page 5 - GameSpy |work=Xbox.gamespy.com |date=2003-01-03 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Carle |first=Chris |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2006/11/21/videogame-babe-of-the-day-helena |title=Videogame Babe of the Day: Helena|work=uk.ign.com |date=2006-11-21 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> [[Pre-order]] bonuses for ''[[Dead or Alive 5 Last Round]]'' offered by [[Amazon.com]] included a downloadable operatic \"Showstopper\" costume for the character.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gameplorer.de/dead-or-alive-5-last-round-release-datum-next-gen/|title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round: Release-Datum f\u00fcr PS4 und Xbox One + Vorbesteller-Boni enth\u00fcllt|work=Gameplorer.de|date=October 24, 2014|language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gameinformer.com/games/dead_or_alive_5_last_round/b/playstation4/archive/2014/10/23/dead-or-alive-5-last-round-coming-february-with-free-trials-in-tow.aspx|title=Dead Or Alive 5: Last Round Coming February With Free Trials In Tow|work=GameInformer.com|first=Mike|last= Futter|date=October 23, 2014}}</ref> One of Helena's outfits in ''Last Round'' is a dress designed by manga artist [[Tamiki Wakaki]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7n7A0HG9s48 |title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round\u2014Tamiki Wakaki Costumes |work=YouTube |date=2015-07-22 |accessdate=2015-09-25}}</ref> while others include downloadable costumes of Reina from ''[[Deception IV: The Nightmare Princess]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/teamninjastudio/status/614040395450748929 |title=Team NINJA on Twitter: \"Helena is Reina, the Princess of Tragedy|work=Twitter.com |date=2015-06-25 |accessdate=2015-09-25}}</ref> Vita Clotilde from [[Nihon Falcom]]'s ''[[The Legend of Heroes: Trails of Cold Steel]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pushsquare.com/news/2015/09/store_update_15th_september_2015_north_america |title=Store Update: 15th September 2015 (North America) |work=Push Square |date= |accessdate=2015-09-25}}</ref> Professor Tierra from [[Square Enix]]'s ''School Girl Strikers'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pushsquare.com/news/2015/11/transforming_schoolgirls_strike_dead_or_alive_5_with_new_costume_crossover |title=Transforming Schoolgirls Strike Dead or Alive 5 with New Costume Crossover |publisher=Push Square |date= |accessdate=2016-01-01}}</ref> and Aquarius from the manga and anime ''[[Fairy Tale]]'',<ref>{{cite web|author=By Sato|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2016/06/09/dead-alive-5-last-round-getting-fairy-tail-collaboration-costumes/ |title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round Is Getting Fairy Tail Collaboration Costumes |publisher=Siliconera |date=2016-06-09 |accessdate=2016-08-29}}</ref> as well as a  ninja outfit<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.the-newshub.com/gaming/ninja-clan-2-costume-pack-available-for-dead-or-alive-5-last-round |title=The real free press |publisher=The-newshub.com |date= |accessdate=2016-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921115042/https://www.the-newshub.com/gaming/ninja-clan-2-costume-pack-available-for-dead-or-alive-5-last-round |archive-date=2016-09-21 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and the Garrison Regiment uniform from ''[[Attack on Titan]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gematsu.com/2016/07/dead-alive-5-last-round-add-king-fighters-mai-shiranui-via-paid-dlc-september |title=Dead or Alive 5: Last Round to add The King of Fighters' Mai Shiranui via paid DLC in September |publisher=Gematsu |date= |accessdate=2016-08-29}}</ref>\n\nAccording to [[IGN]], \"as one of the most technical characters in\" ''Dead or Alive 3'', \"Helena has a truckload of different special techniques and arguably the most powerful punch attacks in the game.\"<ref name=ign2>{{cite web|last=Chau |first=Anthony |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2001/11/15/doa-3-fighter-of-the-day-helena |title=DOA 3 Fighter Of The Day: Helena - IGN |work=uk.ign.com |date=2001-11-15 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> The site added that  her \"fluid motions make her the most graceful fighter\" in the series, and in ''[[Dead or Alive Ultimate]]'', Helena is a \"great mixture of leg and fist strength\" and is \"not the easiest character to master, but when you do master her techniques, you'll dominate.\"<ref name=ign3/> Hardcore Gaming 101 said, \"Her martial arts style, [[Pi Gua Quan]], is not often seen in fighting games, [and] relies on long-hauling circular movements to gain momentum.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/doa/doa.htm|title=Hardcore Gaming 101: Dead or Alive|author=Kurt Kalata and Sam Derboo|work=Hardcore Gaming 101|date=September 3, 2015|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref> Helena is an [[Unlockable (gaming)|unlockable]] character in ''Dead or Alive 4'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox360.gamespy.com/xbox-360/dead-or-alive-4/guide/page_6.html |title=Dead or Alive 4 - xbox360 - Walkthrough and Guide - Page 6 - GameSpy |work=Xbox360.gamespy.com |date=2006-01-24 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> in which she has many \"good 'launcher' attacks\" that can lead into [[Combo (video gaming)|juggle combo]]s, according to [[GameSpy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://xbox.gamespy.com/xbox/dead-or-alive-ultimate/guide/page_24.html |title=''Dead or Alive Ultimate'' Walkthrough and Guide - Page 24 - GameSpy |work=Xbox.gamespy.com |date=2004-01-24 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref>\n\n===In film===\nHelena is a main character in the 2006 live-action film ''[[DOA: Dead or Alive]]'', played by [[Sarah Carter]]. Helena's role of tournament hostess remains intact, but her backstory is ignored and she is given an upbeat personality that contrasts to her aloof in-game disposition; she appears in one scene wearing roller skates, and a line of dialogue has her commenting about wanting to visit Paris. Throughout the movie, Helena is treated as a necessary annoyance by tournament organizer Donovan ([[Eric Roberts]]), who has gained control of DOATEC after the death of Helena's father. She additionally gains a noncanonical love interest in Donovan's technical assistant, Weatherby.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2007/06/15/doa-dead-or-alive|title=DOA: Dead or Alive|author=Stax (Jim Vejvoda)|work=IGN.com|date=June 15, 2007|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n[[File:C2E2 2014 Contest - Helena Douglas (14109313304).jpg|thumb|upright|Noelle d'Arda cosplaying Helena at the [[Chicago Comic & Entertainment Expo|C2E2]] 2014]]\n\nHelena has received mostly positive critical and public reception. Hilary Goldstein of IGN enthused in 2004, \"We love Helena because she's the default ass-kicker. Plus, her home arena, the burning Opera House, is among the coolest in ''DOA Ultimate''. Helena is also the only girl [in the series] that has classic beauty to her. The others play on that Asian school girl vibe men love, but Helena has more class (and bosom, sure) going for her ... the lack of [[slut]] outfits makes her the best dressed.\"<ref name=ign3>{{cite web|last=Goldstein |first=Hilary |url=http://uk.ign.com/articles/2004/09/22/girls-of-doau-helena |title=Girls of DOAU: Helena - IGN |publisher=Uk.ign.com |date=2004-09-22 |accessdate=2015-07-01}}</ref> The site further described Helena as \"gorgeous\" and a \"classy French vixen\".<ref name=ign/><ref name=ign2/> ''Official Dreamcast Magazine'' commented that Helena proved the stereotype of the \"fat opera chick\" to be \"wildly inaccurate.\"<ref name=dm>\"Alive & Heaving\". ''Dreamcast Magazine'' issue 5, page 39.</ref> [[GameFront]] included her among the top video game girls of all time in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.gamefront.com/top-video-game-girls-of-all-time/ |title=Top Video Game Girls of All Time |work=GameFront |date=2007-05-16 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> In 2014, Brazilian site [[GameHall]]'s \"Portal PlayGame\" ranked Helena as the eleventh-most sexy female video character, deeming her the \"most beautiful\" overall in the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://portalplaygame.com/top-100-as-personagens-mais-gatas-dos-games/ |title=TOP 100 \u2013 As Personagens mais gatas dos games &#124; Portal Play Game |publisher=Web.archive.org |date=2015-01-23 |accessdate=2015-07-01 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150123234148/http://portalplaygame.com/top-100-as-personagens-mais-gatas-dos-games/ |archivedate=January 23, 2015 }}</ref> Helena was voted the ''DOA'' series' tenth-most popular character in a fan poll conducted by Koei Tecmo in 2014,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamecity.ne.jp/doa5/lastround/vote/index.html|title=DEAD OR ALIVE 5 Last Round ?|publisher=Gamecity.ne.jp|accessdate=24 December 2014}}</ref> but while she was one of the characters voted by fans to qualify for ''Dead or Alive 3 Xtreme,'' she finished last (ninth) with the fewest percentage of votes.<ref name=\"gamecity\">{{cite web|title=\"DOAX3\"|url=https://www.gamecity.ne.jp/doax3/vote_result.html|website=Gamecity.ne.jp|accessdate=2015-09-19}}</ref>\n\n[[Joystiq]]'s Ludwig Kietzmann questioned \"the practices of Helena Douglas, a supposedly French CEO who dresses for sultry cabaret and literally beats up her employees.\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Kietzmann |first=Ludwig |url=http://www.joystiq.com/2012/09/27/dead-or-alive-5-review/ |title=Dead or Alive 5 review: Begrudge match |publisher=Joystiq.com |date=2012-09-27 |accessdate=2015-06-18}}</ref> AJ Glasser of [[Kotaku]] declared Maria the \"best mom\" in fighting games, \"because nothing says 'Mommy loves you' like taking a sniper's bullet to the heart.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5238770/mommy-dearest-the-best-and-worst-mothers-in-video-games|title=Mommy Dearest: The Best and Worst Mothers in Video Games|first=AJ|last=Glasser|work=Kotaku.com|date=May 6, 2009|accessdate=January 27, 2016}}</ref> However, the site included Fame Douglas among the worst fathers in video games. \"Fame knocks up a world-famous opera singer and then doesn't marry her; but he does leave his daughter his effed up company, DOATEC, after being assassinated. Thanks, Daddy!\"<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://kotaku.com/5297186/father-knows-best-the-best-and-worst-fathers-in-video-games |title=Father Knows Best: The Best and Worst Fathers in Video Games |first=AJ|last=Glasser|work=Kotaku.com |date=June 21, 2009|accessdate=June 18, 2015}}</ref> Helena was named one of the top seven \"hottest girls\" in video game film adaptations by Spanish magazine ''Marca Player'' in 2009.<ref>''Marca Player'' issue 9 page 50.</ref> Her fight scene with Christie placed eleventh in the 2012 \"best cinematic girl-on-girl fights\" online poll conducted by [[JoBlo.com]].<ref>{{cite web|author= Droz (Kevin Blanchard)|url=http://www.joblo.com/hollywood-celebrities/gossip/13115/results |title=HOTTIE POLL: What's the best cinematic girl-on-girl fight? |work=Joblo.com |date=2012-08-04 |accessdate=2016-02-06}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Dead or Alive characters|List of ''Dead or Alive'' characters]] {{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://teamninja-studio.com/doa5/uk/chara19.html}} (''DOA5'')\n\n{{Dead or Alive series}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Fictional businesspeople in video games]]\n[[Category:Characters created by Tomonobu Itagaki]]\n[[Category:Dead or Alive (franchise) characters]]\n[[Category:Female characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional business executives]]\n[[Category:Fictional French people in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional female musicians]]\n[[Category:Fictional Piguaquan practitioners]]\n[[