omatic Relations Between Great Britain and Korea ... dated November 26, 1883.\"</ref>\n| United Kingdom\n|-\n| [[Russia-Korea Treaty of 1884]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc870\ub85c\uc218\ud638\ud1b5\uc0c1\uc870\uc57d(\u671d\u9732\u4fee\u597d\u901a\u5546\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1884<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 32.|page=32}}; excerpt, \"Treaty and Diplomatic Relations Between Korea and Russia. Treaty of Amity and Commerce dated June 25, 1884.\"</ref>\n| Russia\n|-\n| [[Italy-Korea Treaty of 1884]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc870\uc774\uc218\ud638\ud1b5\uc0c1\uc870\uc57d(\u671d\u4f0a\u4fee\u597d\u901a\u5546\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1884<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 32.|page=32}}; excerpt, \"Treaty and Diplomatic Relations Between Korea and Italy. Treaty of Friendship and Commerce dated June 26, 1884.\"</ref>\n| Italy\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Treaty of 1885]]*<br>([[Japan-Korea Treaty of 1885|Treaty of Hanseong]])\n| {{lang|ko|\ud55c\uc131\uc870\uc57d(\u6f22\u57ce\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1885<ref>Yi, Kwang-gyu and Joseph P. Linskey. (2003). {{Google books|8BJyAAAAMAAJ|''Korean Traditional Culture,'' p. 63.|page=63}}; excerpt, \"''The so-called ''Hanseong Treaty'' was concluded between Korea and Japan. Korea paid compensation for Japanese losses. Japan and China worked out the Tien-Tsin Treaty, which ensured that both Japanese and Chinese troops withdraw from Korea''.\"</ref>\n| Japan\n|-\n| [[France-Korea Treaty of 1886]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc870\ubd88\uc218\ud638\ud1b5\uc0c1\uc870\uc57d(\u671d\u4f5b\u4fee\u597d\u901a\u5546\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1886<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 32.|page=32}}; excerpt, \"Treaty and Diplomatic Relations Between Korea and France. Treaty of Friendship, Commerce, and Navigation dated June 4, 1886.\"</ref>\n| France\n|-\n| [[Austria-Korea Treaty of 1892]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc870\uc624\uc218\ud638\ud1b5\uc0c1\uc870\uc57d(\u671d\u5967\u4fee\u597d\u901a\u5546\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1892<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 32.|page=32}}; excerpt, \"Treaty and Diplomatic Relations Between Korea and Austria. Treaty of Amity and Commerce dated July 23, 1892.\"</ref>\n| Austria\n|-\n| [[China-Korea Treaty of 1899]]\n| {{lang|ko|\ub300\ud55c\uad6d\u00b7\ub300\uccad\uad6d\ud1b5\uc0c1\uc870\uc57d (\u5927\u97d3\u570b\u5927\u6df8\u570b\u901a\u5546\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1899\n| Qing (China)\n|-\n| [[Belgium-Korea Treaty of 1901]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc870\ubca8\uc218\ud638\ud1b5\uc0c1\uc870\uc57d(\u671d\u767d\u4fee\u597d\u901a\u5546\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1901<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 32.|page=32}}; excerpt, \"Treaty and Diplomatic Relations Between Korea and Belgium. Treaty of Amity and Commerce dated March 23, 1901.\"</ref>\n| Belgium \n|-\n| [[Denmark-Korea Treaty of 1902]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc870\ub374\uc218\ud638\ud1b5\uc0c1\uc870\uc57d(\u671d\u4e01\u4fee\u597d\u901a\u5546\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1902<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 32.|page=32}}; excerpt, \"Treaty and Diplomatic Relations Between Korea and Denmark. Treaty of Friendship, Commerce, and Navigation dated July 15, 1902.\"</ref>\n| Denmark\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Treaty of 1904]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\ud55c\uc77c\uc758\uc815\uc11c(\u97d3\u65e5\u8b70\u5b9a\u66f8)}}\n| 1904<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 34.|page=34}}; excerpt, \"Treaty of Alliance Between Japan and Korea, dated February 23, 1904.\"</ref>\n| Japan<ref>Note that the Korean Mission to the Conference on the Limitation of Armament in Washington, D.C., 1921-1922 identified this as \"Treaty of Alliance Between Japan and Korea, dated February 23, 1904\"</ref>\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Protocol of August 1904]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc81c1\ucc28 \ud55c\uc77c\ud611\uc57d (\u7b2c\u4e00\u6b21\u97d3\u65e5\u5354\u7d04)}} \n| 1904<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 35.|page=35}}; excerpt, \"Alleged Treaty, dated August 22, 1904.\"</ref>\n| Japan<ref>Note that the Korean diplomats in 1921-1922 identified this as \"Alleged Treaty, dated August 22, 1904\"</ref>\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Protocol of April 1905]]*\n| \n| 1905<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 35.|page=35}}; excerpt, \"Alleged Treaty, dated April 1, 1905.\"</ref> \n| Japan<ref>Note that the Korean diplomats in 1921-1922 identified this as \"Alleged Treaty, dated April 1, 1905\"</ref>\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Protocol of August 1905]]*\n| \n| 1905<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 35.|page=35}}; excerpt, \"Alleged Treaty, dated August 13, 1905.\"</ref>\n| Japan<ref>Note that the Korean diplomats in 1921-1922 identified this as \"Alleged Treaty, dated August 13, 1905\"</ref>\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Treaty of 1905]]*<br>([[Eulsa Treaty]])\n| {{lang|ko|\uc81c2\ucc28 \ud55c\uc77c\ud611\uc57d (\u7b2c\u4e8c\u6b21\u97d3\u65e5\u5354\u7d04)}}<br>({{lang|ko|\uc744\uc0ac\uc870\uc57d(\u4e59\u5df3\u689d\u7d04)}})\n| 1905<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 35.|page=35}}; excerpt, \"Alleged Treaty, dated November 17, 1905.\"</ref>\n| Japan<ref>Note that the Korean diplomats in 1921-1922 identified this as \"Alleged Treaty, dated NOvember 17, 1905\"</ref>\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Treaty of 1907]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\uc815\ubbf87\uc870\uc57d(\u4e01\u672a\u4e03\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1907<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 35.|page=35}}; excerpt, \"Alleged Treaty, dated July 24, 1907.\"</ref>\n| Japan\n|-\n| [[Japan-Korea Treaty of 1910]]*\n| {{lang|ko|\ud55c\uc77c\ubcd1\ud569\uc870\uc57d(\u97d3\u65e5\u5002\u5408\u689d\u7d04)}}\n| 1910<ref>Korean Mission, {{Google books|9OdAAAAAYAAJ|p. 36.|page=36}}; excerpt, \"Alleged Treaty, dated August 20, 1910.\"</ref>\n| Japan\n|}\n\n<nowiki>*</nowiki> [[Unequal treaty]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Korea-related topics]]\n*[[Korean Confucianism]]\n*[[History of Korea]]\n*[[Political factions in Joseon Dynasty]]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{succession box | title=Joseon dynasty politics | before=[[Goryeo politics|Goryeo dynasty politics]] | after= [[Politics of South Korea]]<br>[[Politics of North Korea]] | years=1392&ndash;1897}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Joseon}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Joseon Dynasty Politics}}\n[[Category:Korean Confucianism]]\n[[Category:Joseon dynasty]]\n", "name_user": "Keith D", "label": "safe", "comment": "De-cap", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Politics_of_the_Joseon_dynasty"}
{"title_page": "Hugh Foulkes", "text_new": "{{short description|Welsh footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = Hugh Foulkes\n|image       =\n|image_size  =\n|caption     = \n|fullname    = Hugh Edward Foulkes<ref name=Joyce/>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date|1909|4|13|df=y}}<ref name=Joyce/>\n|birth_place = [[Llandudno]],<ref name=Joyce/> Wales\n|death_date  = {{death year and age|1981|1909}}<ref name=Joyce/>\n|death_place = \n|height      =  \n|position    = [[Left back]]\n|youthyears1 =          |youthclubs1 = \n|years1      =          |clubs1 = [[Llandudno F.C.|Llandudno]]                       |caps1 =    |goals1 = \n|years2      = 1931\u20131937 |clubs2 = [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] |caps2 = 15 |goals2 = 0\n|years3      = 1937\u20131938 |clubs3 = [[Guildford City F.C.|Guildford City]]             |caps3 =    |goals3 = \n|years4      = 1938\u20131939 |clubs4 = [[Darlington F.C.|Darlington]]{{efn|Foulkes also made three appearances for Darlington in the [[1939\u201340 Football League]] season abandoned when the Second World War began. Joyce's ''Football League Players' Records'' counts these matches in its appearance data, although most statistical sources do not.<ref name=Joyce/><ref>{{cite book |first=Frank |last=Tweddle |title=The Definitive Darlington F.C. |publisher=Soccerdata |location=Nottingham |date=2000 |page=41 |isbn=978-1-899468-15-7}}</ref>}} |caps4 = 35 |goals4 = 1\n|nationalyears1 = 1931 |nationalteam1 = [[Wales national football team|Wales]] |nationalcaps1 = 1 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Hugh Edward Foulkes''' (13 April 1909&nbsp;\u2013 1981) was a [[Wales national football team|Wales international footballer]] who played as a [[left back]]. He made his only senior international appearance in a 4\u20130 defeat to [[Ireland national football team (1882\u20131950)|Ireland]] at [[Windsor Park]], Belfast, on 5 December 1931.<ref name=Joyce/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://wfda.co.uk/international_details.php?id=147 |title=Welsh international matches: 5 December 1931 |publisher=Welsh Football Data Archive |accessdate=9 May 2014}}</ref> He played in [[the Football League]] for [[West Bromwich Albion]] and [[Darlington F.C.|Darlington]] in the 1930s. He also played for Welsh club [[Llandudno F.C.|Llandudno]] and in the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] for [[Guildford City F.C.|Guildford City]].<ref name=Joyce>{{cite book |last=Joyce |first=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939 |publisher=SoccerData |location=Nottingham |page=93 |year=2004 |isbn=978-1-899468-67-6}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://coludata.co.uk/item.php?pg=match&pd=1022&it=6 |title=Colchester Utd 5\u20130 Guildford City |website=Coludata |accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Foulkes, Hugh}}\n[[Category:1909 births]]\n[[Category:1981 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Llandudno]]\n[[Category:Welsh footballers]]\n[[Category:Wales international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football fullbacks]]\n[[Category:Llandudno F.C. players]]\n[[Category:West Bromwich Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Guildford City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Darlington F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Southern Football League players]]\n[[Category:Date of death missing]]\n[[Category:Place of death missing]]\n\n\n{{Wales-footy-defender-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = Hugh Foulkes\n|image       =\n|image_size  =\n|caption     = \n|fullname    = Hugh Edward Foulkes<ref name=Joyce/>\n|birth_date  = {{birth date|1909|4|13|df=y}}<ref name=Joyce/>\n|birth_place = [[Llandudno]],<ref name=Joyce/> Wales\n|death_date  = {{death year and age|1981|1909}}<ref name=Joyce/>\n|death_place = \n|height      =  \n|position    = [[Left back]]\n|youthyears1 =          |youthclubs1 = \n|years1      =          |clubs1 = [[Llandudno F.C.|Llandudno]]                       |caps1 =    |goals1 = \n|years2      = 1931\u20131937 |clubs2 = [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] |caps2 = 15 |goals2 = 0\n|years3      = 1937\u20131938 |clubs3 = [[Guildford City F.C.|Guildford City]]             |caps3 =    |goals3 = \n|years4      = 1938\u20131939 |clubs4 = [[Darlington F.C.|Darlington]]{{efn|Foulkes also made three appearances for Darlington in the [[1939\u201340 Football League]] season abandoned when the Second World War began. Joyce's ''Football League Players' Records'' counts these matches in its appearance data, although most statistical sources do not.<ref name=Joyce/><ref>{{cite book |first=Frank |last=Tweddle |title=The Definitive Darlington F.C. |publisher=Soccerdata |location=Nottingham |date=2000 |page=41 |isbn=978-1-899468-15-7}}</ref>}} |caps4 = 35 |goals4 = 1\n|nationalyears1 = 1931 |nationalteam1 = [[Wales national football team|Wales]] |nationalcaps1 = 1 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Hugh Edward Foulkes''' (13 April 1909&nbsp;\u2013 1981) was a [[Wales national football team|Wales international footballer]] who played as a [[left back]]. He made his only senior international appearance in a 4\u20130 defeat to [[Ireland national football team (1882\u20131950)|Ireland]] at [[Windsor Park]], Belfast, on 5 December 1931.<ref name=Joyce/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://wfda.co.uk/international_details.php?id=147 |title=Welsh international matches: 5 December 1931 |publisher=Welsh Football Data Archive |accessdate=9 May 2014}}</ref> He played in [[the Football League]] for [[West Bromwich Albion]] and [[Darlington F.C.|Darlington]] in the 1930s. He also played for Welsh club [[Llandudno F.C.|Llandudno]] and in the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]] for [[Guildford City F.C.|Guildford City]].<ref name=Joyce>{{cite book |last=Joyce |first=Michael |title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939 |publisher=SoccerData |location=Nottingham |page=93 |year=2004 |isbn=978-1-899468-67-6}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://coludata.